description:
# The Power of Loops

Loops let you repeat code multiple times. JavaScript has several types of loops.

## for Loop

The most common loop - great when you know how many times to repeat:

```javascript
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  console.log(`Count: ${i}`);
}
// Output: Count: 1, Count: 2, ... Count: 5
```

## while Loop

Repeats while a condition is true:

```javascript
let countdown = 3;
while (countdown > 0) {
  console.log(countdown);
  countdown--;
}
console.log("Blast off!");
```

## Looping Through Arrays

JavaScript has modern array methods:

```javascript
const fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"];

// Traditional for loop
for (let i = 0; i < fruits.length; i++) {
  console.log(fruits[i]);
}

// Modern forEach
fruits.forEach(fruit => {
  console.log(fruit);
});

// for...of loop (modern and clean)
for (const fruit of fruits) {
  console.log(fruit);
}
```

## Your Quest

Create an array called `levels` containing the numbers 1, 2, 3, 4, 5.

Then use a **for loop** to iterate through the array and print:

**Level 1 complete!**  
**Level 2 complete!**  
**Level 3 complete!**  
**Level 4 complete!**  
**Level 5 complete!**

After the loop, print: **All levels conquered!**

**Tip:** Access array items with `levels[i]` where i is the loop counter.

solutionCode:
// Create a level completion tracker
const levels = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

for (let i = 0; i < levels.length; i++) {
  console.log(`Level ${levels[i]} complete!`);
}

console.log("All levels conquered!");
